items.name: TechNeco Style
items.description:
一种绘画风格lora，用于绘制机能风的日本动漫女孩，看到封面图就会知道它的用途。

对于背景的绘制很差，很难把角色自然地放到背景里

对于prompt，推荐试试uniform,bodysuit,armor这几个

lora的训练使用了NovalAI模型，经过测试对于大部分日本动漫风格模型都有较好的兼容，表现最好的是anything4.5。

高清重绘制推荐使用ESRGAN等算法，而不是使用潜变量，否则会添加过多的细节。

重绘强度在0.3到0.5左右，如果在这种重绘强度情况下重绘依然改变画面结构，推荐使用webui的Antiborn插件，"Stop first pass of highres.fix after this step number “这一选项拉到采样数的3/4左右。另外”Count of final steps to average together“这一选项记得要拉到1以关闭这一功能。

modelVersions.name: v1.1
modelVersions.description:
使用Novalai模型进行训练。

相对于1.0版本,1.1版本对于"armor"这一概念进行了改进。

推荐的lora权重为0.8.

推荐使用Lora block weight插件的OUTALL预设来避免构图的过拟合.

建议使用ESRGAN等放大算法和较低的denoising以避免添加过多细节，我使用了R-ESRGAN 4x+和值为0.4的denoising.

推荐试试的prompt: armor、bodysuit、jacket、uniform.

注意：在示例图像中使用的lora的版本号会与我在这里上传的lora的版本号不一致，这是因为我在本地训练了多个版本。请以我上传的lora的版本号为准。

items.name: Eclair - Kiddy Grade
items.description:
In retrospect I wonder if the name of the series will give me trouble due to a misunderstanding? Regardless, Kiddy grade is one of the great old classic anime with a nice story shrouded in fanservice. I would have tried to add the second version of Eclair but i didn't find enough art and i think i like her first iteration a bit more. All I can say is that Eclair is a quality waifu.

I had good results using: masterpiece, best_quality, highres, <lora:KGEclair:0.7>, KGEclair, yellow_eyes, large_breasts, EclairRedOutfit, cross_earrings, single_thighhigh, thighhighs, gloves, single_earring

While her single thigh high is part of her outfit it sometimes refuses to display it so if you want them better use single_thighhigh and thighhighs, this to prevent it from making them symmetric.

I left her eyecolor as selectable but you should probably add yellow_eyes.

Her earring sometimes tries to pop in a pair so it also a good idea to use single_earring.

Sometimes her gloves morph into long sleeves so if you are invoking her red outfit it is best to add the gloves tag.

I didn't get enough images of her other outfits receptionist or china dress but they are there you might be able to produce them with some luck.

Anyway I'll add the tag summary with the training data so you can experiment.

items.name: Stellaris Portraits LORA
items.description:
Based on the portrait style of the video game Stellaris. There are two different versions since the training results varied quite widely. The versions posted are the top performing epoch from the best two training runs.

Sample images were generated using the simplest possible prompts just the overall style trigger word and a species trigger.

This was my first attempt to put multiple training concepts into a single LORA so some of them don't seem to have taken quite as well as others. I ended up needing to change the trigger word spellings in some cases as using standard spelling was causing issues, some words just couldn't seem to break out during training from whatever the existing meaning for that word in the base model.

items.name: Astronomy Wallpaper
items.description:
Get early access to build and test build, be able to try all epochs and test them by yourself on Patreon or contact me for support on Discord

To support me you can buy me a coffe at https://ko-fi.com/antonioriolo

Training settings:

46 images, 15 steps, 10 epochs, you find many epochs (with test images using plot xy script) on my Patreon while supporting me.

Recommended settings:

  • Make sure you are aware on the usage instructions of LORA

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras (Recommended for best quality, you may try other samplers)

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 10

  • LORA weight for txt2img: i have tryied only 0.7, feel free to try different weights

  • Keys: astronomy wallpaper, spiral galaxy, sun like star, terrestrial planet, gas giant planet

This model is like gambling, many of the images will have no sense and have nothing in common with the prompt, but sometime you get a perfect image of what you want.

I think that's because i added too many concepts in one model only and he gets confused, so sometime you might ask for a star and you would get a galaxy or a planet, like gambling.

I'm uploading epoch 1 that gives more artistic results but if you want to try other epochs with more realistic results come in my patreon.

I didn't experience a lot with this model because today i don't have much time, but if you find good prompts or any good advice for this model, comment/post for the others.

Enjoy!

If you'd like to support my efforts and have access to early and bleeding edge builds, please think about joining my Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/betterCuteAsians

items.name: Violet Monroe
items.description:
📝Biography📝

(generation advice below) 👇

🌟Violet Monroe 🌟

Megan Violet Carlson, who would later be known as Violet Monroe, was born on May 8, 1988, in Minneapolis, Minnesota. She attended a school for music and theater and started her career working at a grocery store at the age of 17. After doing some mainstream modeling, she was contacted by someone in the adult entertainment industry and began performing in adult movies in 2009. Violet has worked for various notable companies in the industry. She has also worked for various renown websites. In her spare time, Violet enjoys singing and studying astronomy.

Violet Monroe, also known as Violet Raye, is a busty and shapely 5'7'' redhead of Dutch and Native American descent, with black and red hair and brown eyes. Her real and natural 34C breasts are complemented by a toned 23-inch waist and shapely 35-inch hips. She has a heart tattoo on her right upper arm and a star tattoo (happy to say, so does my LORA 😏). Violet is based in Los Angeles but has worked all over. With her porcelain skin and sultry presence, Violet Monroe has made a name for herself in the adult entertainment industry.

💡Generation Advice💡

🔧Prompt and Sampling🔧

  • Most images have been generated with LORA weighted @ .75.

  • Most samples done with CyberRealistic v2 and jimEIDOMODE with sampling steps best above 20.

🚀Upscaling🚀

  • Using CyberRealistic, this LORA seems friendly to Hi-Res fix upscaling and the Ulti SD upscale script.

  • Often, I just send it to Ultimate SD upscale after a quick render and run 2x at a scale of two.

  • Ultimate SD upscale script used @ ~.15 - .4 denoising using 8x NMKD Faces or 4X UltraSharp redraw upscalers.

🗒️Side Notes🗒️

  • The prompts continue to evolve. CyberRealistic is a reasonably flexible model for being realism focused. I still think they have trumped the SD 1.5 game. 👑

  • Leave a review if you liked using this.

  • Leave a comment if you are having issues getting good output, I'll try to respond.

items.description:
> <

I made this LoRA because not even anime checkpoints seem to be able to generate this expression on their own.

Usage (important!)

Compatibility

Should work with most anime-like checkpoints. Tested with AOM3 (works best), and MeinaHentai. more testing will be done later.

Weight

I recommend 0.75~1.0; however, should you use other LoRAs with this, try a higher value such as 0.85~1.1

When in doubt, increase weight~! This LoRA impacts artsyle minimally.

Trigger Words

> < is the trigger word. Recommended to put emphasis on this, like (> <:1.2)

Also try one eye closed in your prompt with the above! (may be hard to generate from.)

Limitations

On lower weights and with other LoRAs, this may fail!

Avoid using prompts about the eyes, unless you're using one eye closed with this.

Bias to open mouth. Try (open mouth:1.2) in negative prompt if you need to get around this.

Olivia from Fire Emblem: Awakening, trained on animefull.

Around 0.6-0.8 weight works well.

While I think mine turned out pretty okay, it's very stubborn about using different clothes on higher weights (try adding 'white dress' to the negative) and on lower weights it can really mess up the hair. Also, the dataset used didn't include anything that wasn't her dancer outfit from Awakening, because otherwise it was consistently generating amalgamations of her normal outfit and her FEH alt outfit.

Also, if anyone has any tips for getting well drawn hands more consistently, I'd be glad to hear them. On my setup it takes quite some time per generation, and sometimes it feels like I have to go so many generations just to get something decent and then I gotta fine tune it and it just takes forever lol. Also just any tips in general would be cool, I've only been doing this for a few days and could use the help haha.

Finally, I'll probably make more of these! Super fun to do, and I've already got a couple characters in mind.

items.name: InflateBot (LEGACY; DEV VERSIONS RELEASED)
items.description:
I'm going to be restarting this project with hopefully better organization and methodology!! For now, all my development versions since the first public release have been made available. They're not fantastic, but hopefully one of them does what you need!

InflateBot is a joke that went way too far; originally an attempt to fine-tune GPT2 on inflation erotica, its latest shape takes the form of a LoRA based on the excellent Fluffusion model.

The goal of InflateBot is to provide multi-target inflation and full-body (spherical) inflation that isn't just a featureless blob. Its training data is multi-concept, with folders for the following tags:

  • "air inflation"

  • "blueberry inflation"

  • "floating" (where it coincides with an inflation tag)

  • "hyper inflation"

  • "inflation fetish"

  • "spherical inflation"

The issues targeted by InflateBot are:

  • Over-focusing on belly inflation (ignoring body/spherical/hyper tags)

  • Creating blank spheres with no character at all

  • Creating a sphere that is detached from the character, who may be relegated elsewhere in the image

  • Not generating arms or legs.

In the past, putting "balloon fetish" in the negative prompt helped alleviate some of the issues, but the goal is for that to no longer be necessary. The first demo image below uses this technique, the second does not (Private Version 2 "Oxide" used for these demos)

While InflateBot isn't done yet, I feel like it's far enough along that I'm willing to share some snapshots and see what you guys can do with it! (Note that InflateBot is a LyCORIS, specifically LoHa, and works best with KohakuBlueleaf's a1111-sd-webui-lycoris extension.)

THE OXIDE SERIES USES THE LORA EXTENSION, NOT KOHYA/LOHA LIKE THE OTHERS, POSSIBLY ACCOUNTING FOR INCONSISTENCIES IN MY TESTING. THIS IS MY FAULT.

Hey, long time no update!! I've been busy moving house, and as such, no work has been done on new versions since the last update on the Furry Diffusion Discord server. However, while experimenting with these old versions, I found that this one, which was released to FD but not here, has been giving much better results on full-body inflation than later iterations that were (I believe) unreleased.

Other things that help are putting the trigger tags early in the prompt (as it's expected that the character will take up a lot of space, it's best to block out the shapes for them early) and putting "limbs missing, limbs hidden" in the negative prompt. (This was supposed to be trained into the later versions, I'm not sure if that dataset change made it into this version, but it seems to make a difference regardless.) Dioxide was trained on Fluffusion e12, but works great on e20!!

The plan for the next release is to basically start from the ground up, with a more consistent dataset and more thought put into its structure; however, these "throw things at the wall and see what sticks" experiments are promising.

items.name: Legshow
items.description:
When you're a cis or bi guy, they say you're either a 'boob man', or a 'butt man', or a 'leg man'. Me ? I'm definitely the latter !!! I don't mind a nice rack nor a shapely derriere, and as a sometime-glamor-photographer I've shot plenty of all three.

But show me a set of long, toned legs in a pair of sexy (overpriced) heels, and my heart rate starts going up, my mouth starts going dry, and I find it very hard to focus on anything else.

SD is pretty good at giving me my fix of good gams 'out of the box' ... but if you're anything like me, you're probably thinking "yeah, but it could still be better".

So ... here's my first attempt to address the 'issue'. It's my first working Lora, trained on a set of 244 images of sexy legs, shapely feet, seductive heels, and some appropriate lingerie thrown in. I recommend using a strength of between 0.3-06, and I've found this will generally determine if your shot keeps the rest of your subjects body, or just focuses in on the legs.

"Legshow" is the magic woid, "heels" or "high heels" also encourage good results.

It's definitely not perfect (mixed results with toes, typically require multiple generations, I'm sure inpainting would fix 'em too but hey this is only Week 3 or maybe 4 for me using SD, so proper use of inpainting is waaaay above my skill-level RN haha). I'm sure I'll tweak it some more and update, but pretty happy with it for now ... so ... go nuts :P

Tested in a buncha models as with all my releases, and works. Hell ... even Pixar got the legshow treatment and it worked. Yeesh !

Sara Jean Underwood is an American model, actress and TV host. She was the Playmate of the Month of July 2006, and Playmate of the Year in 2007.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (s4runderwood:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, long brown coat, long haircut, pale skin, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6"

For now I'll leave this version as the main one and I'll keep testing both of them for a while until I make up my own mind. ^^

items.name: Neon Genesis Evangelion 1990s Anime Style LoRA
items.description:
Neon Genesis Evangelion 1990s Anime style LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕


One of the best anime/manga ever made. Use this with AnyLoRA and similar models at around weight 1. Increase the fidelity with the trigger evangelion anime style. Could also help adding anime screencap, 1990s_\(style\) to get more flat colors and 1990s anime noise.

I also suggest you select "None" as the upscaler for highres.fix.
I posted examples using both "None" and R-ERSGAN AnimeVideo, so you can see the difference. The latter is too much "clean" and loses the noise effect.

Keep in mind this is not a character LoRA, so while it can imitate characters from their descriptions (as shown) you might need additional character LoRA/embedding to increase the accuracy. The purpose of this LoRA is to make any character with this style, not only Persona characters.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)
